<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2003-06-13</DATELINE><TITLE>mRNA Cap-1 Methyltransferase in the SARS Genome</TITLE><BODY>The 3D jury system has predicted the methyltransferase fold for the nsp13 protein of the SARS coronavirus. Based on the conservation of a characteristic tetrad of residues, the mRNA cap-1 methyltransferase function has been assigned to this protein, which has potential implications for antiviral therapy.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>